column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , Moderate Snow , Very Light Wind
column14: CHISLED OUT OPENING JUST D/S OF CULVERT, MAJORITY OF MMNT IN FT2 USED 0.6 OF DEPTH AS THE WATER LINE WAS BELOW ICE SURFACE (IE SIGNIFICANTLY BRIDGED).0.5 OF DEPTH WAS APPLIED FOR VERTICALS WHERE BRIDGE ICE WASNT EVIDENT. MMNT IS CONSIDERED VERY POOR. SLUSH ON TOP OF OPEN WATER SECTION WAS NOT MOVING OUT, TECHNICIANS CONSIDER THE MMNT TO REPRESENT ZERO FLOW AT LOCATION. NO EVIDENCE OF PRESSURE RELEASE IN SYSTEM WHEN AUGER HOLE WAS DRILLED FOR DWL AT GAUGE. POTENTIAL FOR GLACIATION U/S OF MMNT SECTION AND/OR ALONG SYSTEM.  **NOTE TO RFT** - UPON INGESTION OF FT2 FILE, IT WAS FOUND THAT FT2 HANDHELD WAS 6MIN 42SEC AHEAD OF PC TIME. START AND END TIME IN EHSN HAVE BEEN ADJUSTED BY 7 MIN TO ACCOUNT FOR THIS DISCREPENCY.  @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ OLD OFFSET = 2.46 RS AT 1542, NEW OFFSET IN BOTH CHANNELS = 2.456 RS USING CALIBRATE FUNCTION IN SL2 FOLLOWING READING OF CUT FROM 1540  Mid-section
